trans-unit.source: Represents a time interval in months and corresponds to the Oracle 9i `INTERVAL YEAR TO MONTH` data type.
The Oracle `INTERVAL YEAR TO MONTH` data type (Oracle 9i or later) contains an interval of time in years and months, and has a fixed size of 5 bytes.
To obtain an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleMonthSpan> object, call the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOracleMonthSpan%2A> method.

Initializes a new <xref href="System.Data.OracleClient.OracleMonthSpan"></xref> structure to the specified number of months.

Initializes a new <xref href="System.Data.OracleClient.OracleMonthSpan"></xref> structure to a specified number years and months.
Number of years.
Number of months.
